From b983c352a43607c718533b38d8274aa210549bb3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 13:36:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.6.1: Expand role access for networking (routes + sidebar
 nav)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Intentional behavior change (not a refactor). Per product spec, the
access model is now:

  - TC/Investor/PML (MEMBER_ROLES): full networking participants.
    Get deal-board, service-requests, pipeline, analytics, plus all
    three /profile/* view routes so any member can browse any other
    member's profile.

  - Admin: oversight only. Gets admin/* routes plus /service-requests
    for workflow observability. No deal-board, pipeline, analytics,
    own-profile, or profile-view routes. Admin does not engage as a
    network member.

Changes vs. pre-T2.6.1 access:
  + TC gets:       /pipeline, /profile/tc, /profile/investor
  + Investor gets: /analytics, /pipeline, /profile/investor
  + PML gets:      /deal-board, /service-requests, /profile/investor
  - Admin loses:   /profile/tc, /profile/pml
                   (admin uses /admin/members for member oversight)

Files (2):
  - src/lib/routes.jsx (+20/-9, net +11)
      Added MEMBER_ROLES constant.
      Reworked access grants per spec.
      Added /profile/investor route (was missing entirely — the
      InvestorCard 'View Profile' link was 404-ing for every user
      before this PR, a side-effect bug fix).
      Updated header comment to reflect T2.6.1's intentional
      behavior-change scope.

  - src/components/layout/Sidebar.jsx (+10/-2, net +8)
      Added Service Requests link to admin sidebar.
      Added Pipeline link to TC and Investor sidebars.
      Added Deal Board + Service Requests links to PML sidebar.
      Added Analytics link to Investor sidebar.
      Added header comment explaining sidebar must stay in sync with
      the authoritative route table in src/lib/routes.jsx.

Scope deliberately limited (part 1 of 2):
  This PR grants ROUTE ACCESS only. Admin can now navigate to
  /service-requests and see the page, but the 'New Request' button
  is still visible to them because this PR doesn't touch the
  component-level role checks. T2.6.2 will follow up to hide
  mutation affordances (Post Deal, Create Request, Apply, etc.)
  when the viewer is an admin.

Verification:
  - Route matrix verified programmatically: all 4 roles match the
    intended access spec exactly
  - npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
  - npm run build: succeeds
  - No pages were modified — only the route declarations and nav
